<div class='page-info span-24'>
  <div class="span-22 append-1 prepend-1">
    <h2>About The Game</h2>
     <!--    http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WZtG__ngTo8  main video
      11     http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dAtzlRgd_lI secondary 
       12     -->
       
    <div class="span-11">
      <p>
        Bug Splat was the first video game I ever created. It was developed in two weeks as an introduction to the Processing
        language during video game design class at UIC. It is a single or multiplayer game created for UIC's or LSU's tactile. The tactile is 
        a multi touch 52-inch LCD tabletop display. All interaction with the game is done with your fingers. The objective of the game is
        very simple, that is to squish, burn, electricute, or blow up all of the bugs any way you prefer.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="span-11 last">
      <p>
        There are really no rules to the game except to kill all the bugs. There are some constraints, that is to kill them and obtain a score higher than 0.
        The longer it takes to kill the bugs the less points you will receive, even negative points. So the objective is to kill them fast! As mentioned, the game 
        is multiplayer, so the more fingers you have the faster the bugs will die, but you also lose points for every touch on the screen, so don't waste your
        touches.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
