  <div class="span-24" id="below-gallery">
    <%= image_tag("horizontal-divider.png") %>
  </div>
  <h2 class="prepend-1">Game Details</h2>
  <div class="span-10 append-1 prepend-1">
      <p>
        Bug Splat is a very simple game when it comes to the engine. Being my first game I was unsure how well processing would handle complete animations
        so each bug only has 2 images it swaps between. This was also due to my lack of photoshop knowledge at the time. The game does contains my first
        iteration of a particle emitter(it is much more refined in the Rise O' The Urchins game). The particle emitter allows a set of images, a direction, max distance,
        and fade time. It was used for the smoke, flames, blood drops, electric arc, and lightning effects.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="span-11 last" >
      <p>
      The music for Bug Splat was taken from Doom 1. This also inspired me to make Bug Splat just that much more gorey, violent, and explosive. So I made sure each
      bug death created a splatter and blood or a smoking corpse. All of the images in some way were drawn or edited by me. 
      </p>
    </div>
</div>
